This directory contains imported PPP control-plane sources derived from
the upstream pppd codebase.

Import scope
- Files under this directory provide the PPP finite state machines and
  control protocols used by the pppox plugin: LCP, IPCP, IPv6CP, PAP,
  CHAP, and supporting utility code.
- The original per-file provenance is preserved in the source headers
  via the upstream copyright and RCS identifiers.

Why these files are vendored
- The pppox plugin needs an in-process PPP control plane that can run
  directly on top of VPP virtual interfaces.
- Real-line validation showed that replacing the imported CHAP/MD5 path
  with a native VPP crypto/hash rewrite broke CHAP authentication, so
  the imported implementation is intentionally retained for correctness.

Local adaptations
- Added per-unit state handling so multiple PPPoX instances can run
  concurrently inside VPP.
- Added the sys-vpp shim layer in sys-vpp.c / sys-vpp.h to bridge the
  imported PPP state machines to VPP/PPPoX runtime hooks.
- Added minimal stubs in ppp_stubs.c for symbols that are not used in
  the VPP environment but are required to build the imported code.
- Kept plugin-facing behavior changes outside the imported files where
  possible, in pppox.c and pppoeclient.c.

Review expectations
- Treat these files as imported third-party sources with localized VPP
  integration changes, not as freshly authored VPP-native code.
- When touching behavior, prefer small, well-contained changes and keep
  the original upstream structure recognizable.
